cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper addresses a boosting method for mapping functionality of neural networks in visual recognition, specifically image classification and face recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also presents a novel approach for generating and learning latent features using the network itself, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper addresses the bias of datasets, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
